.\" Man page for {{ project_slug }}
.\" Contact: {{ author_email }}
.TH {{ project_slug | upper }} 1 "{{ date_now }}" "{{ project_slug }}" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
{{ project_slug }} \- {{ description }}
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B {{ project_slug }}
[\fIOPTION\fR] [\fICOMMAND\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
{{ project_slug }} is a command-line tool that {{ description }}.
.PP
It provides a modern, user-friendly interface with support for configuration,
logging, and various output formats.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help information
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Print version information
.TP
\fB\-\-config\fR=\fIPATH\fR
Path to configuration file (default: ~/.config/{{ project_slug }}/config.toml)
.TP
\fB\-\-color\fR=\fImode\fR
Color output mode: auto, always, never (default: auto)
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-pager\fR
Disable pager for long output
.TP
\fB\-\-verbose\fR, \fB\-v\fR
Increase verbosity (can be used multiple times)
.TP
\fB\-\-quiet\fR, \fB\-q\fR
Decrease verbosity (suppress non-error output)
.TP
\fB\-\-debug\fR
Enable debug output
.TP
\fB\-\-install\fR
Install shell completions and initialize configuration
.TP
\fB\-\-uninstall\fR
Remove shell completions and configuration
.TP
\fB\-\-man\fR
Display this man page
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
\fBconfig\fR
Manage configuration (show, reset, validate)
.TP
\fBdaemon\fR
Manage daemon processes (start, stop, restart, status, list-jobs, cancel-job)
.TP
\fBcompletion\fR
Generate shell completion scripts (bash, zsh, fish, elvish, powershell)
.TP
\fBdoctor\fR
Run diagnostics and health checks (all, config, daemon, terminal)
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
\fB{{ project_slug | upper }}_DEBUG\fR
Enable debug mode
.TP
\fB{{ project_slug | upper }}_LOG\fR
Set log level (error, warn, info, debug, trace)
.TP
\fB{{ project_slug | upper }}_QUIET\fR
Enable quiet mode
.TP
\fBNO_COLOR\fR
Disable colored output (takes precedence over --color)
.TP
\fBRUST_LOG\fR
Set Rust tracing log level
.SH FILES
.TP
\fI~/.config/{{ project_slug }}/config.toml\fR
User configuration file
.TP
\fI~/.local/share/{{ project_slug }}/\fR
Data directory for logs, cache, etc.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Show help:
.PP
.RS
.nf
{{ project_slug }} --help
.fi
.RE
.PP
Run with verbose output:
.PP
.RS
.nf
{{ project_slug }} --verbose
.fi
.RE
.PP
Show configuration:
.PP
.RS
.nf
{{ project_slug }} config show
.fi
.RE
.PP
Generate shell completions:
.PP
.RS
.nf
{{ project_slug }} completion bash
.fi
.RE
.PP
Run diagnostics:
.PP
.RS
.nf
{{ project_slug }} doctor all
.fi
.RE
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
0
Success
.TP
1
General error
.TP
2
Usage error (invalid arguments)
.TP
3
Configuration error
.TP
4
Network error
.TP
5
Permission error
.TP
124
Timeout
.TP
130
Interrupted (SIGINT)
.SH BUGS
Report bugs at: {{ repository_url }}/issues
.SH SEE ALSO
The full documentation is available at: {{ documentation_url }}
